-- South African Agency Will Publish Inflation One Week Earlier From January
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-12-06T06:10:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/south-african-agency-will-publish-inflation-one-week-earlier-from-january.html
South Africa will publish consumer-
inflation data one week earlier from January 2011, Statistics
South Africa said.  The statistics will be announced at 10 a.m. on the second-
last Wednesday of every month, the Pretoria-based agency said in
an e-mailed statement today. The figures are currently announced
at 11:30 a.m. on the last Wednesday of every month.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  